May 23, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.

(1)
First Avenue at N.W. corner of 111th Street, showing sidewalk vendors of dry goods. This picture was taken on the day of the Feast of Our Lady of Mt. Carmel.
July 16, 1934.

(2)
The same, looking north on First Avenue, earlier the same year.
May 23, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

The same, a close-up of the young man in the left foreground of No. 2.
